  String timelineBytesKb(num n);

  /// File size in megabytes, e.g. “1.5 MB”. The number arrives pre-formatted as a string (may contain a decimal point). “MB” is the unit abbreviation; use the target locale's convention.
  ///
  /// In en, this message translates to:
  /// **'{n} MB'**
  String timelineBytesMb(String n);

  /// File size in gigabytes, e.g. “2.3 GB”. The number arrives pre-formatted as a string (may contain a decimal point). “GB” is the unit abbreviation; use the target locale's convention.
